05/03/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police have arrested a Bosnian Serb suspected of committing war crimes and genocide against Muslims in the 1995 Srebrenica massacre, prosecutors announced on Wednesday (March 4th). 
According to a brief statement, the State Protection and Investigation Agency (SIPA) arrested Zeljko Ivanovic in Pale and turned him over to the war crimes prosecutor's office. 
(Dnevni Avaz - 05/03/09; Reuters, Blic, Tanjug, Beta, Glas Srpske - 04/03/09)
